<HEADLINE> Child Killed in Chicago Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A 7-year-old girl was killed
and three others, including a 3-year-old boy, were injured when
they were caught in the crossfire of an apparent gang shooting in
a park in Chicago's western suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Franklin Park police say the two children were walking toward
an ice cream truck Friday afternoon when gunfire erupted from two
nearby cars, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
Both children, the driver of the truck and another man were
shot. The little girl, identified as Juana Nieto, was pronounced
dead a short time later.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver, who was reportedly shot in the head, and the
3- year-old boy are both in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The other man was shot in the chest. He managed to drive two
blocks to a gas station where he sought help. He was taken to an
area hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
