<HEADLINE> AL Chief Calls for Common Arab Stance Towards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the Arab
League (AL) Esmat Abdul-Meguid said today that it was necessary
for the Arabs to adopt a common stance towards Israel's
intransigence in peace process.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark during a meeting here with President of
the United Arab Emirates Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan al-Nahyan.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the AL resolution on freezing the Arab-Israeli
normalization moves adopted early this week in Cairo, Abdul-Meguid
said the decision was a binding one in line with the resolutions
of the Arab summit held in Cairo last June.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Abdul-Meguid expressed appreciation for
the UAE president's support for the AL role and for the Arab
solidarity and unity of the Arab rank in the face of the current
stalled peace process.
</P>
<P>
He briefed al-Nahyan on the results of the Euro-Arab
Cooperation Conference held Thursday in Dubai, one of the seven
emirates in the UAE. The conference was aimed at bolstering the
Euro-Arab cooperation and supporting the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Meguid arrived in Dubai Wednesday to attend the
three-day Euro-Arab Cooperation Conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
