<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic and Hirszon Keep Croatia Hope Alive in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Croatian hero Goran Ivanisevic and
his partner Sasha Hirszon ousted Austria's Thomas Muster and Udo
Plamberger on Saturday to keep Croatia's chances alive in a Davis
Cup Euro-African Zone Group One tie in Graz, Austria.
</P>
<P>
Austria leads 2-1 after Croatia swept the doubles in straight
sets, 7-5, 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's action, Ivanisevic, who was forced to concede the
first singles of the tie Friday due to his leg cramps in the fifth
set against Gilbert Schaller, showed no sign of trouble, beating
their strong rivals easily.
</P>
<P>
``They're a really good doubles team. Goran has such a serve
that we're permanently under pressure,'' said Austrian coach
Ronnie Leitgeb.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's Muster-Ivanisevic duel - the world No. 2 against the
world No. 5 - was expected to be a tough match for both. ``Thomas
certainly won't have it easy,'' said Leitgeb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
