<DOCNO> XIE19970406.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Tries to Avoid Political Crisis Over Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Refoundation Party of
Italy today reaffirmed its opposition to the Italian-led
multinational protection force (IPF) in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The party's general secretary, Fausto Bertinotti, told
reporters that "there is no room for compromise... We will vote
against the military mission in Albania."
</P>
<P>
Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi warned Bertinotti on Friday
that if the Communists do not support the mission in the Balkan
country, his government could fall.
</P>
<P>
The Communists opposed the IPF mission in a parliamentary
debate earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
Bertinotti said his party does not intend to endanger the Prodi
government although it believes that the military intervention in
Albania is flawed from a political or historical point of view.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the center-left Olive Tree Bloc, including the
Communist Refoundation Party, are expected to meet on April 7 to
seek a common ground on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The Olive Tree Bloc formed the Prodi government in April, 1996
after it won 167 of the 315 seats in the Senate and 319 of the 630
seats in the Chamber of Deputies (lower house) in the elections.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the Italian IPF, to be deployed in Albania in the
week beginning on April 14, will protect aid shipments to the
crisis-ridden country as well as the delegations from the European
Union and the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe
to restore order there.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said the Italian government has a duty to help Albania,
adding that "the government has made a long-term plan and we
cannot pull back now."
</P>
<P>
He said that since it is the first time Italy assumes the
leadership of a multinational mission, Italy has a responsibility
to see it through to the end.
</P>
<P>
Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro today warned against
"dangerous divisions" at home and called for concerted efforts to
help Albania out of crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
