<DOCNO> XIE19970406.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Efforts Urged to Halt Infectious Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Environmental
Program (UNEP) has called for effective management of the
environment to halt emerging infectious diseases.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued by UNEP reaching here today said that
old infectious diseases such as malaria and tuberculosis have
resurged and new diseases like HIV have been discovered during
the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The release pointed out that many emerging and resurgent
infectious diseases may have been attributed to "extreme weather
conditions".
</P>
<P>
Many effects of global climate change on human health would be
adverse unless strict measures are undertaken to reduce
greenhouse gas emissions to the reasonable levels, it added.
</P>
<P>
Human interference with the natural flow of freshwater systems
has accelerated the spread of some infectious diseases while dams
and irrigation canals often serve as breeding areas for
mosquitoes, the release stressed.
</P>
<P>
Water pollution can spark outbreaks of cholera and dysentery,
said the release which was issued in commemoration of "The World
Health Day" on April 7.
</P>
<P>
The world environment body of UNEP noted that "human health
and that of the environment are intimately interlinked."
</P>
<P>
"Effective management of the environment will help to halt and
eventually stop these diseases," it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970406.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNEP Meeting Decides to set up Committee of Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A resumed meeting of the U.N.
Environment Program (UNEP) has decided to establish a high-level
Committee of Ministers and Officials in Charge of Environment as
a subsidiary organ of the UNEP Governing Council.
</P>
<P>
In a news release issued here today, the resumed 19th session
of the UNEP Governing Council also decided to strengthen the
Committee of Permanent Representatives.
</P>
<P>
The release said the Committee of Ministers would consist of
36 members elected from among members of the United Nations and
its specialized agencies.
</P>
<P>
The committee will have the mandate, among other things, "to
consider the international environmental agenda and to make
reform and policy recommendations to the Governing Council."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the decisions adopted at the two-day me!i3g
which ended here on Friday, UNEP Executive Director Elizabeth
Dowdeswell said, "this is a great step forward for the
environment."
</P>
<P>
"We now have a global forum for environment ministers which is
a means of keeping environmental issues at the top of the
international political agenda," she noted.
</P>
<P>
The next regular session of UNEP Governing Council will be
held in May 1999 and a special session to examine the results of
the forthcoming U.N. General Assembly Special session is planned
in November this year.
</P>
<P>
The 19th session opened on January 27 and was temporarily
adjourned on February 7 owing to the differences on the reform of
the governance structure of the UNEP.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, UNEP Governing Council adopted the
"Nairobi Declaration on the Role and Mandate of UNEP", which
declares that UNEP should serve as the world's leading
environmental authority.
</P>
<P>
The Nairobi declaration will be presented to the U.N. special
session which is to review and appraise the implementation of
Agenda 21 adopted at the Earth Summit five years ago in Rio de
Janeiro, Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
