<HEADLINE> African Trade Fair Exhibitors Robbed in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Robbers attacked visitors and
participants in the on-going All Africa Trade and Tourism Fair in
a hotel in Kaduna, northern Nigeria on Friday, carting away cash
and property at over five million Naira (about 60,000 US
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sources here said today that the hoodlums unleashed terror at
the Zakariya Prestigeious Hotel, one of the best in the inland
industrial center, between 2:15 and 3:30 Friday morning, breaking
into guest rooms and asking for money and valuables from the
victims at gun point.
</P>
<P>
The victims include participants from other parts of the
country and foreign nationals, who were robbed of cash, wrist
watches, jeweleryious, television sets, cameras, mobile phone
sets, shoes, bags, telecommunication radio sets and some goods
for exhibition.
</P>
<P>
TV, video and radio sets belonging to the hotel were also
carried away, while lodgers without any substantial money and
valuable to offer the marauders were beaten up, amidstryious
screams from the female guests terrified by the gun-totting men.
</P>
<P>
There is no report of any intervention of the hotel security
people during the robber's one-hour operation.
</P>
<P>
Around 10 workers of the hotel have been arrested by police,
while some of the panic-gripped lodgers have reportedly checked
out.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair, jointly sponsored by the Organization of
African Unity and African Economic Community, has attracted
delegates from more than 20 African countries, as well as
business people from all over Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian government announced earlier that security has
been tightened up since the nine-day fair opened on March 29 to
ensure a safe and care-free environment for participants and
visitors. 
</P>
