<HEADLINE> Jordanian Prince Defends Jerusalem From Jewish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Jerusalem should be made the
permanent gate for peace, said Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan here
today at a conference on Israeli settlement policy in Jerusalem,
Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Hassan reiterated Jordan's firm opposition against Israeli
government's Jewish settlement policy in Arab's East Jerusalem,
which the Palestinians claim as the capital of their future state.
</P>
<P>
About 450 dignitaries from a number of Arab and Muslim
countries attended the conference and discussed practical measures
to defend Jerusalem from Jewish settlement and to preserve the
Arab and Muslim identity of the Holy City.
</P>
<P>
The high number of participants at the conference reflected
Arab concern over the plans by the right-wing Israeli government
to consolidate the Jewish state's grip on East Jerusalem
highlighted by its latest plan to build a Jewish settlement on
Jabal Abu Ghneim, local press reports said.
</P>
<P>
Three major religions in the world -- Islam, Judaism and
Christianity -- all consider Jerusalem as their religions' birth
place. Israel, a Jewish state, has been accused by the
international community of Judaising the Holy City by building
Jewish settlement there.
</P>
<P>
Israeli government's settlement policy has triggered off
consistent opposition from the Arab world and stone-throwing
incidents in the West Bank. 
</P>
