<HEADLINE> Rolf Sorensen Wins Tour Of Flanders World Cup Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Dane Rolf Sorensen broke away on
the long home stretch to win the Tour of Flanders World Cup
classic in Meerbeke, Belgium, Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sorensen beat his closest challengers Frederic Moncassin of
France and Italy's Franco Ballerini by five seconds. The top three
made their vital break with 9 kilometers to go after ten riders
were still packed together following the 15 steep hills that
dotted the 256-kilometer trek through Flanders fields.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's Andrei Tchmil finished fourth, 17 seconds behind,
ahead of Italians Davide Casarotto and Claudio Chiappucci.
</P>
<P>
The World Cup classic was run under a brilliant sunshine,
considerably easing race conditions. Pre-race favorite Johan
Museeuw, was accidentally run into the ground by Swiss Bruno
Boscardin some 30 kilometers from the end and lost all hope for a
third win in the famed classic over the cobblestones and hills of
northern Belgium.
</P>
<P>
World Cup leader Erik Zabel, who won Milan-San Remo two weeks
ago, was never a factor in the second World Cup race of the season.
</P>
<P>
The next event in the World Cup competition is the
Paris-Roubaix classic on the cobblestones of northern France next
weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
