<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Middle East peace process is
near collapse because of the Israeli government's failure to abide
by the signed agreements, Syrian Vice President Zuhair Masharqa
said.
</P>
<P>
In an article published today by Syrian newspaper Al-Baath,
Masharqa warned of the emergence of tension that might bring the
region back to violence because of Israel's disregard for the
Madrid conference and the U.N. relevant resolutions.
