<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region Using Overseas Funds for Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region will need a great deal of overseas funds if it
is to speed up housing construction as planned, the regional
construction department says.
</P>
<P>
Some 31.5 million sq m of residential buildings will be built
by the year 2010, and will need 20 billion yuan in funds.
</P>
<P>
To accelerate construction work, funds from both China and
abroad will be needed, sources say, and policies will be made to
attract outside funds.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, per capita living space for 16,000 people
was less than four sq m., and 700,000 sq m of housing needed
repairs. In addition, the regional urban population is expected to
grow at an annual rate of 50,000, requiring 800,000 sq m of new
housing.
</P>
<P>
The regional government is planning to have 11 sq m in per
capita living space for its citizens by 2010.  
