<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor Urges Development of New Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Song Jian, who is
also minister in charge of the State Science and Technology
Commission, today urged authorities in China's northwest to
further emancipate their mind and to give priority to developing
high and new technology for local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Song heard reports from the Shaanxi Provincial government in
Xi'an on the construction of the State Yangling Agricultural High
and New Technology Demonstration Area from April 3 to 6 and
visited a series of local economic activities.
</P>
<P>
He has made explicit statements about the development of the
Yangling demonstration area and emphasized that a new mechanism
must be found for developing the area instead of sticking to
outmoded methods.
</P>
<P>
The new research centers should also pay attention to both
scientific development and their use to combine agricultural
technology with economic development in a better way, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged local authorities to find young scientists
from both inside and outside China to develop Yangling into a
major investment and development area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
