<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Cooperation With Italy: NPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of China's National People's
Congress (NPC) Qiao Shi said here today that China attaches great
importance to developing friendly relations and fostering
cooperation with Italy.
</P>
<P>
Italy, as a major member of the European Union, is playing an
increasingly important role in European and international affairs,
Qiao said during a meeting with Italian Senate President Nicola
Mancino.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chief, who arrived here Saturday for a week-long visit,
also expressed satisfaction with the development of the relations
between China and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral ties have developed smoothly since the two
countries established diplomatic relations 26 years ago, he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, he said, top leaders of the two
countries have increased the exchange of visits and cooperation
between the two countries in the political, economic and cultural
fields and in science and technology has been enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade is also on the rise, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said there is a great potential and bright future for the
two countries' economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said China and Italy have identical or similar views on
major international issues and to develop 21st century-oriented,
long-term and stable relations between the two countries is not
only in the fundamental interests of the two countries and two
peoples but is also conducive to world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Mancino welcomed Qiao's visit to Italy and agreed with Qiao's
assessment of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries enjoy very good relations and he
had been to China and witnessed great changes that have taken
place there.
</P>
<P>
Italy is willing to further develop its relations with China,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Italy is the third leg of Qiao's four-nation tour. He had
visited France and Norway and will continue on to Mongolia.
</P>
</TEXT>
