<HEADLINE> Wanda Maintains Four-Point Lead in China's Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian Wanda
maintained its four-point lead in China's professional soccer
league after beating Qingdao Hainiu 1-0 in the fifth round on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wanda registered a perfect record of 5 wins in as many outings
this season and also stretched their unbeaten record to 39 matches.
</P>
<P>
Their closest rival Shanghai Shenhua scored four unanswered
goals in the match against the Chinese army August First Sunday
thanks to a hat-trick by Xie Hui. The other goal was scored by
Zhu Qi.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, which won the league title in 1995 and finished
second last year, has registered 11 points from three wins and two
draws.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Apollo played a couragous away match against Tianjin
Lifei in Tianjin and forced the home team to a goalless draw.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Hongyuan, the other team from Guangdong in the
12-team professional league, was beaten at home, losing 2-0 to
Sichuan Quanxing.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the season, Guangdong Hongyuan was beaten 4-1 by
Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Marcelo Marmelo de Silva again staged a sole drive
and opened the scoring for Sichuan Quanxing at the 74th minute.
Yao Xia added a goal for Sichuan at the 80th minute.
</P>
<P>
De Silva, who is in his third season with Quanxing, chested
down a pass from Ma Mingyu in the middle of the pitch and dribbled
it into the penalty area to beat charging-out goal-keeper Ou
Chulian with a low shot.
</P>
<P>
The win put Sichuan Quanxing in the fourth place with eight
point, one point behind Guangzhou Apollo.
</P>
<P>
In other matches played on Sunday, Jinan Taishan scored its
first win of the season by beating Yanbian Aodong 1-0 while
Vanguards Huandao forced Beijing Guo'an to a goalless draw.
</P>
</TEXT>
