<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Time Is Pressing for HKSAR Stationery Printing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong government printers
will be working extra time rolling new official stationery off the
 presses in the remaining 80-odd days before the Special
Administrative Region (SAR) is formed, the Hong Kong Standard
newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Official letterheads, envelopes, documents and forms bearing
new logos and revisions must be ready for the new SAR government.
</P>
<P>
"Compared with the normal workload, our output in the next few
months is expected to increase by at least 30 to 50 percent,"
Chief Printing Superintendent John Tse Tak-man was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"We are concentrating on general stationery at the moment, but
the workload will get much heavier as more and more documents are
confirmed."
</P>
<P>
He said it is difficult to estimate the total amount of
stationery to be printed, but disclosed that the police force
alone needed 1,000 different forms bearing a new logo.
</P>
<P>
On top of stationery, the Government Printing Department was
also awaiting orders for official handover publications to be
handed out during various ceremonies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
