<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.8
degrees on the Richter scale jolted Saturday night Bojnourd city
in Khorasan province, about 600 kilometers northeast of Tehran,
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 23:14 hours local time, destroyed
a number of residential houses, the report said, however, it did
not mention casualties.
</P>
<P>
Two earthquakes measuring 5.4 and 6.1 degrees on the Richter
scale hit several cities in Khorasan province on February 5,
killing about 1,000 people and injuring hundreds of others.
</P>
<P>
The quakes also damaged 11,000 houses in over 100 villages,
making thousands become homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
