<HEADLINE> Iranian Parliament Speaker to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq-Nouri is to visit Russia Thursday as a major campaign
for Iran's 7th presidential elections scheduled for May 23,
today's English daily Iran News reported.
</P>
<P>
The 54-year-old speaker, a front-runner among nominees in the
current presidential race, will make the five-day visit to Russia
at the invitation of Russian State Duma Speaker Gennady Selezney.
</P>
<P>
However, the daily said that Nateq-Nouri's visit is part
of Iran's effort to counter U.S. anti-Iran propaganda. Iranian
Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati waged extensive visits to
Islamic countries last month with invitations from Iranian
President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani to his counterparts for the
Organization of Islamic Countries summit scheduled to be held
here in December.
</P>
<P>
Russian Ambassador to Tehran Sergei Tretyakov termed the
visit to Moscow, the capital of Russia, of the Iranian parliament
speaker as a major step toward strengthening relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Iranian authorities said earlier that the visit by
Nateq-Nouri to Moscow has been postponed due to the likelihood
of drastic changes in the Russian government.
</P>
<P>
While stressing importance of strategic relations between the
two countries, Nateq-Nouri said earlier that consolidation of
Tehran-Moscow ties will have positive and constructive impacts
on all regional and world countries.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming visit by the strong presidential candidacy
shows that the Iranian regime attaches greater importance to its
strategic relations with northern neighbor of Russia, which has
already sold three submarines and nuclear reactors to Iran
despite strong opposition by the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
