<HEADLINE> Israel Eases Closure on West Bank, Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli army today eased
the closure imposed on the West Bank and Gaza Strip following a
relatively quiet weekend, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The new arrangements, which take effect this morning, allow
Gaza Strip residents in the West Bank to return to Gaza, as well
as West Bank residents in the Gaza Strip to travel home.
</P>
<P>
The army is also letting Palestinians who are married to
Jerusalem residents with Israeli identity cards to enter the
city.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, another 22 Palestinian ambulances are allowed to
enter Israel on an emergency basis, bringing to 36 the number of
ambulances allowed to cross into Israel from the Palestinian
autonomous areas.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army said that 100 Arab laborers working in tourist
industries are also allowed to enter Israel as of this morning,
but stressed that all entrance permits are subjected to strict
security clearances.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Israel imposed a total closure on the West Bank
and Gaza Strip immediately after a suicide bombing attack in a
down town coffee shop in Tel Aviv, which left three women dead
and more than 40 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The closure has barred tens of thousands of Palestinians from
returning to their jobs inside Israel and from traveling
between the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
