<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Sustaining its steep decline for
the second week in succession, India's annual rate of inflation
shed 0.14 percentage points to 7.51 percent for the week ending
March 22, the Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The Inflation rate stood at 4.9 percent during the
corresponding period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the official Wholesale Price Index (WPI) for "all
commodities" (base 1981-82=100) for the week under review too
declined. It stood at 322 (provisional) as against 322.2
(provisional) for the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The decline in inflation is attributed to lower prices of
commodities such as fruits, vegetables, eggs and poultry chicken.
</P>
</TEXT>
