<HEADLINE> Zambia Not to Be Used to Attack Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will not allow its
territory to be used as a launching pad for attacks against Zaire
but will let countries use its facilities for humanitarian
reasons.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Zambian Foreign Minister Lawrence Vshimba
here on Saturday while commenting on reports that Belgium has
sent an advance party of soldiers into Zambia in readiness for
the evacuation of its nationals in Lubumbashi, capital of Zaire's
Shaba province adjacent to Zambia.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Belgian army press office in Brussels
said, "in the framework of its mission, the Belgian detachment at
Brazzaville will send a recconnaissance team to Ndola in Zambia.
Its aim is to prepare the evacuation of our nationals in
Lubumbashi.''
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the number of Belgian nationals in
Lubumbashi ranges from 500 to 1,500.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian foreign minister said that Zambia has no problem
to accommodate the Belgians if they are coming for humanitarian
reasons while the country cannot accommodate them if they want to
make Zambia a base for attacking zaire.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that rebal forces in eastern Zaire are
advancing to Lubumbashi, second largest city of Zaire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
