terrorism and told the Uruguayan ambassador that Iran expects the
Uruguayan government to provide additional security measures for
protecting the Iranian embassy staff in Montevideo.
</P>
<P>
"Iran would like to see the speedy arrest of the masked
terrorists," the Iranian official was quoted by the report as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan ambassador deplored the incident and called it
a grave problem against the credibility of his country.
</P>
<P>
He was confident that based upon the two countries' excellent
relations his government would spare no efforts in pursuing the
matter and announcing the result of the investigations. 
