<HEADLINE> Quicker, Greener Access to HK Government Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Daily Information Bulletin
(DIB), issued by the Hong Kong Government Information Services
(GIS), has been uploaded onto the Government Home Page on the
Internet since April 1.
</P>
<P>
Internet users can now read the DIB, which covers all the press
releases and regular statistics and figures issued through GIS by
various government departments, under the News Update of the page.
</P>
<P>
A GIS spokesman said today that the new arrangement was
environment-friendly, as more than 3.1 million sheets of A4-size
paper could be saved each year, not to mention the postage, labor
and other costs incurred in printing and mailing.
</P>
<P>
At present, 853 copies of the Chinese and English versions of
the DIB are sent daily to subscribers, including local and
overseas public organization, consulates and the business
community.
</P>
<P>
It will no longer be sent to subscribers in the form of hard
copies from May 1.
</P>
<P>
"Internet users can now view the DIB the day immediately after
the press releases have been issued, compared with two or three
days through the normal mailing method," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Major press releases issued by policy branches and government
departments have already been included in the Internet since the
end of 1995, yet the launch of the DIB on the Internet provides a
more comprehensive set of government press releases which Internet
users might find useful."
</P>
<P>
The News Update in the Government Home Page attracted more than
5,400 visitors in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
