<HEADLINE> Tanzania Joins Committee To Fight Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is among five
African countries picked to form the continental ad hoc committee
to co-ordinate the ratification and implementation of the United
Nations Convention to Combat Desertification (UNCCD).
</P>
<P>
A government press release said this here on Saturday adding
that other committee members are Burkina Faso, Senegal, Tunisia,
Nigeria and Congo.
</P>
<P>
The committee chaired by President Blaise Campaore of Burkina
Faso, was nominated during the ministerial Pan African Conference
on the implementation of UNCCD and the follow up of the results
of the United Nations Conference on Environment and Development
(UNCED) held at Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso from March 18 to 21
this year.
</P>
<P>
The meeting ovserved that 23 out of 50 African countries had
by last month ratified the convention since June, 1994 when the
convention was globally adopted.
</P>
<P>
The continental conference urged all African states and
governments yet to ratify the convention to do so immediately
before an internnational conference to assess the development
meets in Paris, France in September this year. 
