<HEADLINE> Overhaul of Italy's Development Aid System Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said here today he was planning an overhaul of Italy's
development aid system, especially to define the responsibilities
of the government and of the parliament on aid.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a conference on aid policies, Dini said the
government's job is to work out and introduce policies, and it is
for the parliament to approve the plans and the expenditure on aid
in a three-year period of time.
</P>
<P>
Responsibility for aid would stay with the foreign ministry,
but management of the program would be entrusted to a development
agency and the Service Center for Training, he added.
</P>
<P>
Dini stressed the need to separate development aid from Italy's
commercial policies.
</P>
<P>
Dini had called for reforming the country's development and
welfare systems from January 1995 to January 1996, when he acted
as prime minister of Italy.
</P>
<P>
On issues of Bosnia and Albania, Dini said, "these were
situations in which it is necessary to use a new approach in
tackling not only the emergency but also development and
reconstruction, in a context of stability."  
