<HEADLINE> Big Snowstorm Hits Southern Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 5 (Xinhua) -- An exceptionally big snowstorm,
the worst in 50 years, hit the Kopaonik mountainous area in
southern part of the Republic of Serbia today and blocked all the
roads.
</P>
<P>
The Novinska Agencija Tanjug reported that the snowstorm
swepted across the area at the speed of 100 kilometers per hour,
lowering the temperature to minus nine degrees centigrade.
</P>
<P>
The snow on the ground was 1.36 meter deep in average and five
meter deep in some areas.
</P>
<P>
All attempt to reopen the snow-sealed roads ended in failure as
the huge amount of snow blocked the roads again shortly after they
were cleared. 
</P>
