<HEADLINE> Albania Seeks EC Help in Preparation of General Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha
today urged the European Commission (EC) to offer help to his
country in the coming parliamentary elections scheduled for June
and in drafting a new constitution.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian presidential information office said Berisha put
forward the proposal to a delegation of the EC, currently on a
visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Berisha said free elections are the best and only way to
restore stability in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian authorities have decided to cooperate with the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe and other
international organizations, Berisha said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the EC should play an important role in the
preparation of Albania's general elections.
</P>
<P>
He said it is important to work out, with the EC's help, a
Western-type constitution to help Albania through the present
difficult period.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that on March 9, Berisha and other 10 main
political parties reached an agreement, which provided that the
Balkan country would have an early election in June this year.
</P>
<P>
The present parliament was formed after elections in May last
year, but the opposition headed by the Socialist Party had accused
the ruling Democratic Party of manipulating the elections. 
</P>
