<HEADLINE> New Zealander David Tua Retains WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Unbeaten heavyweight David Tua
of New Zealand retained his title of World Boxing Council (WBC) in
Atlantic City on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tua stopped Oleg Maskaev in the 11th round of a scheduled
12-rounder.
</P>
<P>
Frustrated for 10 rounds by Maskaev's quick jabs and long
reach, Tua was trailing on one judge's card and tied on another
when he forced Maskaev into a corner and unleashed a pair of
thunderous lefts during an eight-punch barrage, dropping him to
his knees.
</P>
<P>
Referee Lindsay Page stopped the fight at 1:16 of the 11th
round.
</P>
<P>
24-year-old Tua boosted his record to 27-0 while 28-year-old
Maskaev, the Kazakstan native living in New York, dropped to
20-2. 
</P>
