<HEADLINE> Canada Beats Finland 2-1 to Earn Title Game Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- On a last-minute goal by Vicki
Sunohara, Canada overwhelmed Finland 2-1 to earn a fourth berth at
the title in the World Women's Ice Hockey Championship in
Kitchener, Canada on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sunohara, making her return to the national team after seven
years, slapped home a pass from Geraldine Heaney with 24 seconds
remaining.
</P>
