the United States and China, in the gold-medal round on Sunday.
Finland will play for the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Canada has never lost a game in any previous worlds on its way
to three gold medals.
</P>
<P>
Finland, a three-time bronze medalist, opened the scoring seven
minutes into the game by Kirsi Hanninen.
</P>
<P>
Hayley Wickenheiser tied it 1-1 on a feed from Angela James in
the second period.
</P>
<P>
Five of the eight teams competing will advance to the 1998
Olympics at Nagano, the first games to include women's ice hockey.
The host country, Japan, has a bye.
</P>
<P>
The four teams playing Saturday earned Olympic berths in the
preliminary round, and Russia and Sweden will vie for the final
opening on Sunday. Switzerland and Norway were eliminated Friday.
