<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Oil Prices Drop Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the crudes
and refined products closed at 15.90 U.S. dollars per barrel last
week, said the Energy and Mines Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The average price estimated for April of 1997 will be 16.23
dollars per barrel, a continual drop from 17 dollars per barrel in
March, 18.70 dollars in February and 20.36 dollars in January.
</P>
<P>
The price fall was a result of seasonal effect of less demand
for energy.
</P>
<P>
However, oil sector sources said the Venezuelan profits from
the export of hydrocarbons will maintain stable during the
April-May-June quarter as a consequence of the price rise in
gasoline in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The average basket price of crudes and byproducts set by the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) was 17.40
dollars per barrel at the close of last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
