<HEADLINE> Chilean President Inaugurates Metro Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
today inaugurated Line Five of the Metro, which is expected to
meet the demand of transport in the east of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The 10.3 kilometer-long new line, with 12 stations, will start
with 10 trains, each with six coaches, to serve 17,000 travelers
daily.
</P>
<P>
With the start of the new line, which begins at Baquedano and
ends at Bellavista de la Florida, the Metro network will increase
38 percent to 37.6 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the line cost 400 million U.S. dollars and
lasted 42 months.
</P>
<P>
Frei expressed his satisfaction over the advanced technology
adopted in the construction of the new line, including its modern
installations, trains, and equipment.
</P>
<P>
The project shows the institutional and professional capability
of the public sector, since the metro was completed within the
time and budget scheduled, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
