<HEADLINE> Italy Edges Spain to Reach Davis Cup Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 5 (Xinua) -- Unfancied Italy edged Spain on
Saturday by taking a 3-0 lead in their world group quarter-final
tie in Pesaro, Italy on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the doubles match, Italy's Omar Camporese and Diego Nargiso
spent three hours to defeat Spain's Javier Sanchez and Francisco
Roig 5-7, 7-6 (7-0), 6-2, 7-6 (7-5).
</P>
<P>
Italy will play away to either Sweden or South Africa in the
semi-finals in September. Sweden led South Africa 2-1 after
Saturday's doubles match.
</P>
<P>
Australia gualified for a berth in the other semi-final when
Australia's Mark Woodforde and Todd Woodbridge won the doubles
match over the Czech Republic in Adelaide, australia and led
3-0 over their rivals.
</P>
<P>
Australia will take on either the United States or the
Netherlands. The U.S. team led 2-0 ahead of Satureday's doubles
in California. 
</P>
