<HEADLINE> Greece Lifts Three Golds at European Union Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Italy snatched three
and two gold medals respectively at the second day of the European
Union weightliting championships in Pori on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Greek Christos Spirou won the men's 76-kilogram class with a
total weight of 320kgs. He was followed by German Marco
Szyplowski and Swede Andre Aldenhov.
</P>
<P>
Ionna Chatzioannou won Greece's second gold medal at the
women's 64-kg event, lifting a total of 192.5kgs. Italian Katia
Tacuzzo and Spaniard Carmen Caballero finished second and third
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The women's 70-kg title went to Maria Tatsi of Greece, who
lifted 197.5kgs. Susanna Samuelsson of Finland placed second and
Sharon Oakley of Britain was third.
</P>
<P>
Italian Sergio Mannironi lifted 335kgs to win the men's 83-kg
division. Fellow countryman Diego Facco finished second and
Jaarli Pirkkio of Finland placed third.
</P>
<P>
Another Italian Francesco De Tomaso took the men's 91-kg title
with a weight of 347.5kgs. He was followed by Austrians Jurgen
Matzku and Rudolf Kobler.
</P>
<P>
Oliver Caruso of Germany got the 99-kg event after lifting
375kgs. Finland's Janne Kanerva and Spain's Lorenzo Carrio
placed second and third respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
