<HEADLINE> Nigeria Beats Guinea 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Super Eagles beat Guinea's
Syli Nationale 2-1 in a '98 French World Cup soccer qualifier at
the National Stadium in Lagos Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The two teams, both with most of their members playing in
Europe, fought a scoreless first half, though the Nigerians seemed
to have dominated the field.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Amokachi scored the first goal for Nigeria at 20th
minute in the second half, producing an explosion of joys among
anxious Nigrian fans.
</P>
<P>
He scored the second goal 10 minutes later with a small angle
shot just near the goal.
</P>
<P>
Titi Camar, a Guinean star called back from Frence, showed his
value when he fought through several Nigerian players to score the
only goal for his team, five minutes to the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's victory put Nigeria at the No. 1 place in Group A in
the African region, with seven points in pocket, as it had beat
Burkina Faso 2-0 and forced a 1-1 draw with Kenya earlier.
</P>
<P>
Guinea, with six points in hand before Sunday's game, after
beating Kenya 3-1 and Burkina Faso 2-0, will drop to the second
place.
</P>
<P>
Kenya and Burkina Faso, who both had played two games, now
score one point and zero respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
