<HEADLINE> Nigerian City to Hold Cultural Carnival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Calabar City will stage
its first international cultural carnival on April 28 to promote
itself to the outside world and attract investors.
</P>
<P>
The carnival, tabbed "Crosfact 1997", will feature arts and
craft exhibitions, traditional sports such as boat regatta, and
local cuisines and dances, said Okpo Ojah, the chairman of the
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Africa's own fashions, pharmaceutical industry, local
technology and intellectual property will also be promoted at the
10-day festival, the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
Calabar is a major city in southeastern Nigeria's Cross River
State. The country's first export processing zone went into
operation there recently. 
</P>
