<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Troops to Be Deployed in All Liberian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Soldiers of the West African
peace-keeping force, known as ECOMOG, will be deployed to all the
13 counties of Liberia, as part of strategies to ensure
security in preparation for the country's May 30 elections.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a meeting on Friday between the
ECOMOG High Command and the newly-inducted Liberian Electoral
Commission, the News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted ECOMOG Commander Major-General Victor Malu as
saying that with the expansion of troops in 33 towns in Liberia,
the troops are expected to carry out patrols in surrounding
villages.
</P>
<P>
He told Henry Andrews, chairman of the commission, that ECOMOG was
ready to render all necessary assistance to facilitate the smooth
discharge of the responsibility toward the conduct of the elections.
</P>
<P>
Such assistance would include transportation, effective
communication as well as stationing the troops physically at the
electoral booths.
</P>
<P>
Malu also assured the commission that full security would be
provided for all the commission members.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his thanks to ECOMOG for the assurance of support,
Andrews said the commission was satisfied with the efforts by
ECOMOG to ensure security in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The recovery of unsurrendered weapons in the country has
further built confidence of the Liberian people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
